  "text": "The Firefox TLS connection chain from the networking layer to the crypto layer proceeds through four hops:\n\n**Hop 1 — netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpConnection.cpp (`nsHttpConnection`)**\nThe `nsHttpConnection` class in `netwerk/protocol/http/nsHttpConnection.cpp` is the top-level HTTP connection object. When a new HTTPS connection is activated (via `OnSocketConnected`), it calls `mTlsHandshaker->SetupSSL(mInSpdyTunnel, mForcePlainText)` to initiate the TLS setup. The `TlsHandshaker` is a helper object owned by `nsHttpConnection` that manages the TLS handshake lifecycle. The file `netwerk/protocol/http/TlsHandshaker.cpp` implements `TlsHandshaker::SetupSSL` and `TlsHandshaker::InitSSLParams`, which retrieve the `nsITLSSocketControl` interface from the socket transport and configure ALPN/NPN protocol negotiation before the handshake begins.\n\n**Hop 2 — security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.cpp + nsNSSIOLayer.h (`nsSSLIOLayerHelpers`)**\nThe `nsSSLIOLayerHelpers` class is declared in `security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.h` and implemented in `security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.cpp`. This class bridges Necko's socket layer to NSS. The key entry point is `nsSSLIOLayerAddToSocket()` (in `nsNSSIOLayer.cpp`), which: (1) obtains or creates an `nsSSLIOLayerHelpers` instance (public or private browsing), (2) creates an `NSSSocketControl` info object, (3) pushes a plaintext observer shim layer onto the NSPR file descriptor stack, and (4) calls `nsSSLIOLayerImportFD()` which invokes `SSL_ImportFD()` to wrap the raw NSPR fd with an NSS SSL layer and registers handshake callbacks (`HandshakeCallback`, `SSL_AuthCertificateHook`, etc.).\n\n**Hop 3 — security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.cpp (`nsNSSIOLayer` integration)**\nThe same file `security/manager/ssl/nsNSSIOLayer.cpp` implements the NSS I/O layer integration. The function `nsSSLIOLayerImportFD()` calls `SSL_ImportFD(nullptr, fd)` to create the NSS SSL socket, then registers all the necessary NSS callbacks (handshake callback, secret callback, client auth hook, certificate auth hook). The `nsSSLIOLayerHelpers` class also defines the NSPR layer identity (`nsSSLIOLayerIdentity`) and the layer method table (`nsSSLIOLayerMethods`) that NSS uses to intercept I/O operations.\n\n**Hop 4 — security/nss/lib/ssl/sslsecur.c and ssl3con.c (actual TLS handshake)**\nThe actual TLS handshake is performed in the NSS library. `security/nss/lib/ssl/sslsecur.c` contains `ssl_Do1stHandshake()` — the core handshake state machine driver — and `SSL_ForceHandshake()`, which drives the handshake to completion. `ssl_Do1stHandshake` loops calling `ss->handshake(ss)` until the handshake function pointer is cleared. The TLS 1.2/1.3 handshake messages (ClientHello, ServerHello, etc.) are implemented in `security/nss/lib/ssl/ssl3con.c`, which contains `ssl3_SendClientHello()` (sends the initial ClientHello), `ssl3_HandleServerHello()`, and the full TLS record processing logic (`ssl3_HandleRecord`)."
}

